radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal left basal atelectasis. A small hiatal hernia. The liver enhances normally without focal concerning lesion. No biliary ductal dilation. The gallbladder is normal. Bilateral renal cortical scarring likely reflects prior injury/infection. No concerning renal lesions, no hydronephrosis. Mild fat stranding along the anterior abdomen superior to the emboli kiss without underlying discrete abnormality of the transverse colon or stomach. A tiny fat containing umbilical hernia. Appendix markedly abnormal with submucosal edema, surrounding fat stranding and dilation up to 12 mm consistent with acute appendicitis. No signs of perforation. The colon contains a mild fecal load. A pessary noted in the vaginal vault. The uterus and adnexal structures appear normal. Urinary bladder is unremarkable.
